ares with and departs from Descartes, Hegel, Marx, Heidegger, Weil, Lacan, Merleau-Ponty, and Lyotard, elucidating “the sharing of voices,” in Nancy’s phrase, between Nancy and these thinkers.Contributors: Georges Van Den Abbeele, Emily Apter, Rodolphe Gasché, Werner Hamacher, Eleanor Kaufman, Marie-Eve Morin, Timothy Murray, Jean-Luc Nancy, and John H. Smith  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aLiterary Studies. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Deconstruction.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aDeconstruction.  aFeminism.  aJean-Luc Nancy.  aMarxism.  aPhenomenology.  aPhilosophy.1 aAbbeele, Georges Van Den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aApter, Emily, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGasché, Rodolphe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoh, Irving, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoh, Irving, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHamacher, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaufman, Eleanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Ian Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorin, Marie-Eve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurray, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNancy, Jean-Luc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, John H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVan Den Abbeele, Georges, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075167340uhttps:/